'''明'''（{{lang-en|'''Ming the clam'''}}，約1499年－2006年）是一只[[北极蛤|北极蛤]]，截至目前是已知最长寿的多細胞個體动物<ref name="sciencenordic"/><ref name="Farrar ">{{cite news|url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/uk_news/article74394.ece|title=Ming the mollusc holds secret to long life|last=Farrar|first=Steve|date=2007-10-28|accessdate=2013-09-01|work=The Sunday Times|location=伦敦|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203023553/http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/uk_news/article74394.ece|archive-date=2013-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=telegraph>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1567562/Clam,-405,-is-oldest-animal-ever.html|title=Clam, 405, is oldest animal ever|last=Alleyne|first=Richard|accessdate=2008-07-26|work=The Daily Telegraph|location=伦敦|date=2007-10-28|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080606074620/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1567562/Clam,-405,-is-oldest-animal-ever.html|archive-date=2008-06-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最初年齡經推算達到405歲，相當於出生在中國[[明朝|明朝]][[万历|万历]]年间（1601年），后来更正到507岁，即出生在1499年（[[弘治_(明朝)|弘治]]十二年），因此得名“明（Ming）”<ref name=cnwest>{{cite news|url=http://news.cnwest.com/content/2007-10/29/content_1060854.htm|title=世界最长寿动物为蛤类 可以存活405年(图)|publisher=陕西新闻网|work=北京晨報|date=2007-10-29|author=廖亚平|accessdate=2013-11-14|language=zh-cn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203175416/http://news.cnwest.com/content/2007-10/29/content_1060854.htm|archive-date=2013-12-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="gb"/>。

==發現==
2007年10月28日，英國《泰晤士報》報導，在前一年（2006年）[[威爾士|威爾士]][[班戈大學|班戈大學]]海洋科学学院的研究者在[[大西洋|大西洋]]北部的[[冰岛|冰岛]]海底發現并捕捞到了3000多个空贝壳和34个存活個體<ref name="cd">{{cite web |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hqbl/2007-10/29/content_6213326.htm |title=世界最长寿动物是冰岛海底蛤类“明” |accessdate=2013-11-14 |publisher=中国日报 |date=2007-10-29 |language=zh-cn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610195707/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hqbl/2007-10/29/content_6213326.htm |archive-date=2015-06-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他們按照常規，把明及其他撈獲物放進冰箱內，並未有留意到明的長壽<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/environment/animals/scientists-killed-worlds-oldest-living-creature-20131115-2xkpr.html |title=Scientists killed world's oldest living creature |date=2013-11-15 |publisher=[[雪梨晨報|The Sydney Morning Herald]] |language=en |access-date=2013-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123174714/http://www.smh.com.au/environment/animals/scientists-killed-worlds-oldest-living-creature-20131115-2xkpr.html |archive-date=2013-11-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這是一种圆蛤类软体动物，长约8.6厘米，因其在生長過程中，每一年殼體都會長出一條大約0.1毫米的紋理，从其贝壳上的环状紋理判断，它的年龄介于405至410岁之间<ref name="gb">{{cite web |url=http://gb.cri.cn/12764/2007/11/07/2945@1833612.htm |title=最长寿动物以明朝命名 |accessdate=2013-11-14 |publisher=世界新闻报 |date=2007-11-07 |language=zh-cn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203002157/http://gb.cri.cn/12764/2007/11/07/2945@1833612.htm |archive-date=2013-12-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。来自[[班戈大学|班戈大学]]的研究人员阿伦·瓦那梅克博士和海洋科学教授克里斯·理查森等人执行了这项研究，他们将其放置在冷冻柜里以待后续研究<ref name="abc"/><ref name="people">{{cite web |url=http://world.people.com.cn/n/2013/1114/c157278-23539188.html |title=世界最老生物507岁高龄 比之前估测多百岁(图) |accessdate=2013-11-14 |publisher=人民网 |date=2013-11-14 |language=zh-cn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202232100/http://world.people.com.cn/n/2013/1114/c157278-23539188.html |archive-date=2013-12-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。最初的估计显示明在被发现以前已经活了405年，但科研人员对这一数字并不确定<ref name=telegraph/><ref name="abc">{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2007/10/29/2072637.htm |title=405-yr-old clam dredged from the deep |accessdate=2007-10-29 |publisher=ABC News |date=2007-10-29 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071029091034/http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2007/10/29/2072637.htm |archive-date=2007-10-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="BBC">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7066389.stm | work=BBC News | title=Ming the clam is oldest mollusc | date=2007-10-28 | accessdate=2010-05-12 | language=en | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100517093446/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7066389.stm | archive-date=2010-05-17 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==確定年齡==
明自被捕撈上岸后放置在冷冻柜里以待后续研究，在随后进一步研究其年龄的过程中死亡，当时班戈大学的研究人员打开了它的壳，以进一步对其进行分析，结果发现明的生命迹象逐渐消失<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.163.com/13/1114/11/9DKV5RJA0001121M.html|title=世界最老动物507岁蛤蜊被科学家撬壳杀死(图)|author=王菁|accessdate=2013-11-14|publisher=中国日报网|location=北京|date=2013-11-14|language=zh-cn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131117164357/http://news.163.com/13/1114/11/9DKV5RJA0001121M.html|archive-date=2013-11-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。2013年11月13日公佈的分析表明其真实年龄高达507岁，比此前预估的要再多100多岁<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-2505155/Worlds-oldest-creature-confirmed-507-years-old-scientists-KILLED-shellfish.html |title=World's oldest creature is revealed to be 507-year-old shellfish called Ming – until scientists KILLED it by opening it up to check its age |accessdate=2013-11-13 |publisher=Daily Mail |date=2013-11-13 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113233620/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-2505155/Worlds-oldest-creature-confirmed-507-years-old-scientists-KILLED-shellfish.html |archive-date=2013-11-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://world.people.com.cn/n/2013/1114/c157278-23539188.html|title=世界最老生物507岁高龄 比之前估测多百岁(图)|author=王菁|accessdate=2013-11-13|publisher=中国日报网|date=2013-11-13|language=zh-cn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202232100/http://world.people.com.cn/n/2013/1114/c157278-23539188.html|archive-date=2013-12-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這意味，明大約出生在公元1499年，也就是[[哥倫布|哥倫布]]第一次抵達美洲的幾年之後<ref name="sciencenordic"/>。修正后的年齡估計值經證實採用了包括[[放射性碳定年法|碳-14測定法]]在內的多重方法，海洋生物学家罗布认为，這個數值很可能精确到1-2年内<ref name="sciencenordic">{{cite web |url=http://sciencenordic.com/new-record-world%E2%80%99s-oldest-animal-507-years-old |title=New record: World’s oldest animal is 507 years old |author=Lise Brix |work=Sciencenordic |publisher= |language=en |date=2013-11-06 |accessdate=2013-11-14 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131115121158/http://sciencenordic.com/new-record-world%E2%80%99s-oldest-animal-507-years-old |archivedate=2013-11-15 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。海洋科学家保罗·巴特勒表示：“第一次我们计算有误，也许那时我们正忙于出版我们的发现结果而有点草率。但我们现在能绝对确认我们得到了正确的数字。”<ref name="ch">{{cite web |url=http://news.china.com/international/1000/20131114/18147034.html |title=世界最老生物507岁高龄！比之前估测多百岁(图) |accessdate=2013-11-14 |publisher=中国日报网 |date=2013-11-14 |language=zh-cn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611004142/http://news.china.com/international/1000/20131114/18147034.html |archive-date=2015-06-11 |dead-url=no }}</ref>此前，明已經以405歲高齡得到了吉尼斯世界纪录的认证<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.cnnb.com.cn/system/2013/11/14/007904124.shtml|title=世界最老生物507岁高龄！被科学家不小心弄死啦|author=郭静|accessdate=2013-11-15|publisher=中国宁波网|date=2013年11月14日|language=zh-cn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610225327/http://news.cnnb.com.cn/system/2013/11/14/007904124.shtml|archive-date=2015年6月10日|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。鉴于其年龄，这只北极蛤被以“[[明朝|明朝]]”命名。理查森说，明的发现可以帮助科学家了解有些动物是如何达到如此长寿的<ref name="Farrar "/>。

